		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Memblers wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Looks like you forgot to clear the name/attrib table.</div><br />How? The init code I use is copied almost verbatim from what I posted <a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?t=19" class="postlink">here</a>, and it writes $00 bytes to PPU $2400-$2BFF, which should cover H- and V-mirroring. Did you test it on a 1-screen or 4-screen mapper or a CHR RAM mapper or something? Oh wait, it doesn't write the entire palette, only the part that it actually uses ($3F00-$3F03). Is that important?<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">For the pitch bends, if anyone wants to do a slow or shallow one, it would almost have to be a lot finer than a semitone.</div>
<br />I'm still trying to think of the most efficient way to express those. Which NSFs make good use of shallow pitch bending?

		

