		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Should NES musicians fear Bananmos?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Given that hardware for Game Boy Advance and Nintendo DS homebrew was easier to get at the time, I decided to wait before making a serious NES music engine until the PowerPak was released. It was in short supply for the first year, but once I got my hands on one at the end of 2008, I made the first version of what is now known as <a href="https://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?f=6&amp;t=13589" class="postlink">Pently</a>.<br /><br />And by now, there are a lot of users willing to run tests using PowerPak, EverDrive, or INL-Retro, which are about as easy to get and use as the GBA and DS flash solutions of old.<br /><br />So I guess we can consider this case closed.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
